Guidelines.

- To create a new revision, use the command below:
    alembic revision --autogenerate -m "the name of your revision"

- To upgrade the tables in your database, use the command below:
    alembic upgrade <revision identifier> (in the revision file find the variable "revision")

- To downgrade the tables in your database, use the command below:
    alembic downgrade <revision identifier> (in the revision file find the variable "down_revision")
